    en: {"title":"How to cut business costs with automation","description":"Not \"add AI\" — remove specific hours of manual work. A breakdown of where automation actually saves money and how fast it pays back.","h1":"How to cut business costs with automation","sections":[{"title":"Short answer","paragraphs":["Costs drop from one precise decision, not from \"using AI\" in general: remove one recurring step — moving data between CRM and email, assembling an invoice, answering a routine question.", "Across our projects that means 40–80% time savings on routine operations, with payback from 3 months — calculated before the scope is signed, not after."]},{"title":"What usually breaks","paragraphs":["Companies buy an \"AI platform\" license before identifying which process actually eats the most hours — the tool sits idle and costs keep climbing.", "The working order is the reverse: audit processes and data first, calculate ROI per scenario, then pick the tool — CRM automation, an integration, or an AI layer on top of existing systems."]},{"title":"4-week plan","paragraphs":["Week 1 — audit: how many hours and where the team loses them, ROI for 2–3 scenarios. Weeks 2–3 — a pilot on one process with a measurable effect. Week 4 — compare actuals to the estimate and decide whether to roll out to adjacent processes."]},{"title":"How Bober AI Systems helps","paragraphs":["An automation audit starts at 150,000 ₽ and takes 1–2 weeks; if you move to implementation, that fee is credited against the project budget.", "After that: a fixed scope, a production launch, and documentation handed to your team — no demos that nobody opens a month later."]}],"faq":[{"q":"How much can automation actually save?","a":"Across Bober AI Systems projects, 40–80% of employee time on routine operations, with payback from 3 months — calculated during the audit, before the scope is signed."},{"q":"Where to start on a limited budget?","a":"With an audit of one process from 150,000 ₽ (1–2 weeks). It maps loss points and priorities, and its cost is credited toward implementation if you continue."}]},
