    en: {"title":"How to eliminate manual work between systems","description":"Manually moving data between CRM, email, and Excel is the top cause of errors and lost time. How to build one connected loop instead.","h1":"How to eliminate manual work between systems","sections":[{"title":"Short answer","paragraphs":["Manual work between systems disappears not from \"automation in general\" but from API or webhook integrations between specific system pairs: website → CRM, CRM → 1C, email → task tracker.", "Wherever data has no single source of truth, it lives in PDFs, Excel, email, and the CRM at once — that's exactly the loop that needs to become one flow."]},{"title":"What usually breaks","paragraphs":["Teams automate one system in isolation — say, the CRM — and forget the neighboring points: accounting, warehouse, support. The copy-pasting just moves to the next seam.", "The second risk is integrating without error monitoring: if a webhook fails silently, manual work comes back within a month and nobody notices right away."]},{"title":"4-week plan","paragraphs":["Week 1 — map systems and manual transfer points. Weeks 2–3 — API/webhook integrations for the 1–2 most frequent pairs. Week 4 — sync error monitoring and handover documentation."]},{"title":"How Bober AI Systems helps","paragraphs":["We map where data gets lost between CRM, 1C, documents, email, and messengers, and connect them into one working loop — no manual copying.", "Deployment happens in your cloud or your own on-prem environment when that's a security requirement, not a technology choice for its own sake."]}],"faq":[{"q":"How do you find out where manual work is actually costing time?","a":"With a process and data audit: we log which systems staff manually move information between and how many hours a week that takes."},{"q":"Can you remove manual work without replacing the CRM?","a":"Yes — in most projects we don't replace the CRM, we connect it via API to 1C, email, and messengers so data flows automatically."}]},
